## Overview

This project scaffolds a [Google ADK](https://google.github.io/adk-docs/) agent and exposes
it as a production-ready HTTP API via FastAPI. The agent is accessible through three endpoints:

| Endpoint | Method | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `/health` | GET | Liveness check — always returns `{"status": "ok"}` |
| `/run` | POST | Send a prompt and receive the full agent response |
| `/stream` | POST | Send a prompt and receive a streaming (SSE) response |

Start the API server and interact with `{{ root_agent.name }}` over HTTP — no ADK SDK required
on the client side.

## Generated Files

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `agent.py` | ADK agent wiring — topology, model, tools |
| `tools.py` | Tool implementations (deterministic and LLM-facing) |
| `callbacks.py` | Audit logging and guardrail hooks |
| `main.py` | ADK `Runner` entry point for local execution |
| `api_server.py` | **FastAPI server** — exposes `/health`, `/run`, `/stream` |
